node.text: Andrew Huberman (@hubermanlab) took his first jiu jitsu class with me at @10patx in Austin while visiting. As the picture shows, I think it went well. See video on my YouTube page. It's great to see a world-class scientist like Andrew humbly take on a new challenge with a beginner's mind.

node.text: Education is about more than memorization. Learning & practicing general principles of problem solving is more important than memorizing the techniques of how to solve specific problems.

node.text: I went back on @joerogan's podcast yesterday. Joe is one of my favorite people to talk to in this world, on and off the mic. We discussed robots, Tesla Autopilot, AI, jiu jitsu & went down some rabbit holes. Whiskey was involved, plus a Bukowski poem at end. It's on Spotify now.

node.text: This is me at 10 months old. I spent much of my childhood smiling, in love with the world, the magic of it all. I still am, even more so, but smile on the inside ;-) Thanks for the birthday wishes. Time flies and this ride ends too quickly but thank you for making mine a fun one.

node.text: I'm doing an experiment of reading/rereading 1 book a day for 7+ days starting Aug 19. Looking for short, impactful books (see pic for examples). Recs appreciated. I'll share the list before & thoughts after. Join me in reading. Vote on full list by clicking link in profile.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Lex Fridman on August 10, 2021. May be an image of 3 people, people standing and indoor.

node.text:
It's great to be back to training, 10 rounds of live rolling. The look on my face is that of someone who just got run over by a train. On the right is @gabe_tuttle, head instructor of @10PATX in south Austin. On the left is @craigjonesbjj, one of the best grapplers on the planet, and as you can tell by the rash guard also one of the funniest.

It's an honor to get to hang out and train with these guys. 10th Planet in South Austin is a great school. I'm there on occasion, in case you want to train with me, but regardless I recommend it highly.

Also Craig and some other incredible grapplers have already or are soon moving to Austin. I can't wait to learn from and train with these guys.
